# Ignore-rect mask for probability_edit_smoke (NumOS SDL2 emulator visual test).
#
# Reason: the ONLY volatile region on this ProbabilityApp screen across separate
# launches is the StatusBar clock. This script edits the mu parameter to 2.5 and
# lets the app recompute the normal PDF/CDF and redraw the bell curve (now
# centered at 2.5); after the commit the editor is closed, so there is no blinking
# input cursor and no animation once the 200 ms fade-in settles — the body
# (parameter panel, PDF/CDF readout, bell curve) is byte-stable. The clock label
# is drawn by StatusBar::updateClock() from the real wall clock (time() ->
# localtime -> "%02d:%02d", src/ui/StatusBar.cpp), so HH:MM reflects the minute
# each scripted run happens to execute on. Two launches in different minutes (or
# hours) therefore differ only inside the clock glyphs. This is expected
# per-minute UI nondeterminism, NOT a renderer bug — the renderer is frozen, so it
# is masked in the comparator instead of edited in src/.
#
# Region: the SAME shared StatusBar clock as probability_smoke / statistics_smoke
# / settings_smoke / math_showcase_smoke. The label is aligned LV_ALIGN_LEFT_MID,6
# in lv_font_montserrat_12 (StatusBar.cpp:61-65) and is always exactly 5 glyphs
# ("HH:MM"), so its box spans ~x[6..38] y[8..16]. Because both the HOUR and the
# MINUTE digits can vary across arbitrary launches, the mask covers the WHOLE
# label, not just the minutes.
#
# Rect = full HH:MM label box (~x[6..38] y[8..16]) padded ~2px on each side ->
# x[4..40] y[6..18]. This is tight to the clock: the app title is centered
# (x~160), the battery/angle/modifier are right-aligned (x>240), and the
# Probability body (parameters + bell curve recentered at mu=2.5) renders below
# the y=24 StatusBar separator — none are masked.
#
# x,y,w,h
4,6,37,13
